# fate - Chinese baby name creator using
#         traditional bazi (eight characters)
#         + wuxing (five elements) numerology
#         (Go, MIT)
#
# Author : babyname (godcong + collaborators)
# Upstream: https://github.com/babyname/fate
#
# `fate` generates Chinese baby names using
# traditional Chinese numerology principles:
#   - **Bazi** (八字 / "eight characters"):
#     the four pillars of destiny based on
#     birth time + date - year + month +
#     day + hour each map to two
#     characters from the Heavenly Stems +
#     Earthly Branches
#   - **Wuxing** (五行 / "five elements"):
#     the elemental cycle - metal + wood +
#     water + fire + earth; each Chinese
#     character has an elemental
#     classification
#   - **Sancai-Wuge** (三才五格): the
#     "Three Talents and Five Grids" name
#     numerology system that scores names
#     by stroke count combinations
#   - **Tone harmony** (平仄): pingze tonal
#     pattern matching for euphonic
#     pronunciation
#
# Architecture:
#   - **Bazi calculator** (godcong/chronos
#     for lunar calendar + bazi
#     calculation)
#   - **Yi calculations** (godcong/yi for
#     I Ching numerology integration)
#   - **Character database** (SQLite +
#     XLSX-derived dictionaries of
#     Chinese characters with stroke
#     counts + element classifications +
#     traditional meanings)
#   - **Configurable scoring**
#     (config.json defines weighting
#     across multiple criteria)
#   - **Multi-format output** (text +
#     CSV + JSON; configurable via
#     FileOutput section)
#
# Distinguishing features:
#   - **Bazi-aware** (incorporates
#     traditional Chinese birth-time-
#     based destiny calculation - most
#     name generators ignore this)
#   - **Wuxing balance** (suggests names
#     that complement the missing
#     elements in the child's bazi)
#   - **Sancai-Wuge scoring** (numerical
#     scoring of name combinations based
#     on traditional stroke-count
#     numerology)
#   - **Last name + birth time inputs**
#     (constrains generation to match
#     existing family name + auspicious
#     time)
#   - **Sex-specific filtering**
#     (different character pools +
#     scoring for male vs female names)
#
# Use cases:
#   - Expectant parents seeking
#     traditional Chinese names with
#     numerological consideration
#   - Calligraphy + tattoo design (find
#     characters matching specific
#     elemental + numerical criteria)
#   - Academic research on Chinese
#     naming conventions
#   - Cultural appreciation projects
#
# Usage:
#   fate <command> [flags]
#
# Subcommands (cobra):
#   init                           - generate
#                                     default
#                                     configuration
#                                     file
#   name                           - generate
#                                     names
#                                     based on
#                                     birth
#                                     details
#   check                          - verify
#                                     environment
#                                     correctness
#                                     (timezone
#                                     data
#                                     etc.)
#   version                        - show
#                                     fate
#                                     version
#
# `init` flags:
#       --path <dir>               - output
#                                     directory
#                                     for
#                                     config
#                                     file
#                                     (default
#                                     current
#                                     directory;
#                                     creates
#                                     config
#                                     .json)
#
# `name` flags:
#   -l, --last <surname>           - set
#                                     last
#                                     name
#                                     (Chinese
#                                     surname
#                                     character)
#   -b, --born <date>              - birth
#                                     date/
#                                     time
#                                     in
#                                     format
#                                     YYYY/MM/
#                                     DD HH:MM
#                                     (default
#                                     current
#                                     time)
#   -p, --path <dir>               - input
#                                     config
#                                     path
#                                     (default
#                                     ".")
#   -o, --outout <dir>             - output
#                                     directory
#                                     for
#                                     generated
#                                     name
#                                     file
#                                     (note:
#                                     "outout"
#                                     is the
#                                     upstream
#                                     flag
#                                     name -
#                                     typo
#                                     preserved
#                                     for
#                                     compatibility)
#   -s, --sex                      - sex of
#                                     the
#                                     baby
#                                     (default
#                                     false =
#                                     female;
#                                     true =
#                                     male)
#
# Standard:
#   -h, --help                     - show
#                                     help
#   -V, --version                  - show
#                                     version
#
# Example invocations:
#   # Initialize default config
#   fate init
#
#   # Initialize config in specific dir
#   fate init --path /etc/fate
#
#   # Generate names for a boy born now
#   fate name -l 王 -s
#
#   # Generate names with specific birth
#   # time
#   fate name -l 李 -b "2024/06/15 14:30" -s
#
#   # Female baby (default sex flag)
#   fate name -l 张 -b "2024/03/20 09:15"
#
